ce:section.ce:para:
In this work, an “on-off-on” fluorescence strategy for KMnO4 and AA detection was established based on fluorescent AuNCs@ZIF-8, which was fabricated through the incorporation of AuNCs into the cavities of ZIF-8 (Scheme 1
                     ). According to the fluorescence quenching effect of KMnO4 on AuNCs@ZIF-8 nanoprobe, the limit of detection (LOD) for KMnO4 is 10 nM. Subsequently, the AuNCs@ZIF-8/KMnO4 is utilized for detecting AA. Due to the strong reduction ability of AA, MnO4
                     − could be easily reduced and the fluorescence quenching effect of KMnO4 on AuNCs@ZIF-8 is inhibited, leading to the fluorescence enhancement of AuNCs@ZIF-8. Benefiting from the enrichment of the cavities structure for analytes, the LOD for AA detection is 37 nM.
